cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CG, cs.CC

The paper deals with problems related to directed graphs and their structures, such as out-branchings and pathwidth. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), which deals with combinatorial and graph-theoretic problems. The paper also uses algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of extremal structures and local search suggests categories such as cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
